  "instruction": "Write a Common Lisp macro `count-calls-to` that temporarily replaces a function with a counting wrapper during execution of the body, restores the original on exit, and returns the call count.",
  "reference_defmacro": "(defmacro count-calls-to (fn &body body)\n  (let ((counter (gensym)) (orig (gensym)) (args (gensym)))\n    `(let ((,counter 0))\n       (let ((,orig (symbol-function ',fn)))\n         (unwind-protect\n              (progn\n                (setf (symbol-function ',fn)\n                      (lambda (&rest ,args)\n                        (incf ,counter)\n                        (apply ,orig ,args)))\n                ,@body\n                ,counter)\n           (setf (symbol-function ',fn) ,orig))))))",
